In this case, you have two groups named "foo" followed by different numbers (123 and 124), which violates this requirement. So the regular expression cannot match any strings, including "aa". If you intended for these two groups to share the same value (i.e., they should both store the letter "a"), then you could combine them into one group like so: `/^(((?!(?P<foo>\w+))[A-Z])|([A-Z]?\d{6}))$/`. This would allow it to match strings such as "Az10" or "Abcdefg", but not strings that do not start with uppercase letters or six consecutive digits at the beginning of the string.
